libeasyfc
------------------------------------------
libeasyfc is an interface library to generate fontconfig configuration for user
preferences. this supports to assign your preferrable fonts to the alias fonts,
such as sans-serif, serif and monospace per languages.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.6-1
  girepository-GLib2.0-1.54.1-2
  girepository-x11-1.54.1-2
  libeasyfc-devel-0.14.0-1bl1
  libeasyfc-gobject-devel-0.14.0-1bl1
  libeasyfc-gobject0-0.14.0-1bl1
  libeasyfc0-0.14.0-1bl1
  libfontconfig-devel-2.13.1-1
  libfontconfig1-2.13.1-1
  libfreetype-devel-2.10.2-2
  libfreetype6-2.10.2-2
  libglib2.0-devel-2.54.3-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.54.3-1
  libharfbuzz-devel-2.6.6-1
  libharfbuzz0-2.6.6-1
  libxml2-2.9.10-1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.10-1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gobject-introspection-1.54.1-2
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://bitbucket.org/tagoh/libeasyfc/

Canonical download:
  https://bitbucket.org/tagoh/libeasyfc/downloads/libeasyfc-0.14.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libeasyfc-0.14.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libeasyfc-0.14.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libeasyfc-0.14.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libeasyfc-0.14.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libeasyfc0-0.14.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libeasyfc-devel-0.14.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libeasyfc-gobject0-0.14.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libeasyfc-gobject-devel-0.14.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/girepository-Easyfc0.14-0.14.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

